<br>
Seriously speaking now, there are a lot of wonderful things that can be accomplished with cloning human cells.  Certain genetic diseases can be fully wiped out.  Organs could be cloned for transplant.  Imagine the lives that could be saved.  Cloning entire people is really not practical at this point due to the mediocre success that science has had in cloning animals, but cloning cells or organs could open new doors to patients who are out of alternatives.<br>
<br>
For example: People with AIDS cannot manufacture white blood cells.  What if white blood cells could be cloned?  Someone with organ damage in need of a transplant could be spared by the cloned organ.<br>
<br>
Everyone is afraid of Frankenstein and man's quest to play God, but we should not let fear blind us to the possibilities of a better world. <p>Ambersky <BR>
